1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
Antibodies are Y-shaped proteins that tag threats for your immune system.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:06,800
But what exactly do they do?

3
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:10,800
When a virus or bacteria invades, antibodies spring into action.

4
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:14,400
They bind to the invaders, marking them for destruction.

5
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:18,000
This helps our immune cells identify and eliminate them.

6
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:23,600
Think of antibodies as the 'CSI agents' of your body, uncovering and tagging threats.

7
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:25,600
Curious about your immune system?

8
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:27,600
Hit follow for more insights!
